  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>

        <div rend="parallel">
          <p xml:id="AN168-kilavi">iravukkuṟi vanta talaimakaṉai <app><lem>iravukkuṟi</lem><rdg wit="#C9v">tōḻi iravukkuṟi</rdg></app> vilakki varaivu kaṭāyatu.</p>
          <p xml:lang="en">How HE who had come for a night tryst was urged for marriage by obstructing the night tryst.</p>
        </div>
        <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="AN168">
        <l><anchor n="1"/>yāma nummoṭu <supplied>ka</supplied>ḻippi nōymikap</l>
        <l>paṉivār kaṇṇēm vaikutu miṉiyē</l>
        <l>yāṉṟal vēṇṭum vāṉṟōy veṟpa</l>
        <l>vallāṉ kuṉṟaṉ paṭuniḻaṟ cērnta</l>
        <l>nallāṉ parappiṟ kuḻumū rāṅkaṭ</l>
        <l>koṭaikkaṭa ṉeṉṟa kōṭā neñci</l>
        <l>ṉutiya ṉaṭṭil pōla voliyeḻun</l>
        <l>taruvi yārkkum peruvaraic cilampi</l>
        <l>ṉīṉṟaṇi yirumpiṭi taḻīik kaḷiṟutaṉ</l>
        <l>ṟūṅkunaṭaik kuḻavi tuyilpuṟaṅ kāppa</l>
        <l>voṭuṅkaḷai pulampap pōka kaṭuṅkaṇ</l>
        <l>vāḷvari vayappuli kaṉmuḻai yuraṟak</l>
        <l>kāṉavar maṭinta kaṅkuṉ</l>
        <l>mā<supplied>ṉa</supplied>tarc ciṟuneṟi varuta ṉīyē.</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
        <l>Having spent midnight with you, as pain increases (1)</l>
        <l>we would rest now, our eyes overflowing with tears. (2)</l>
        <l>[This] has to end, o man from the sky-touching mountain, (3)</l>
        <l>– your coming along the small paths [that are] the track of deer, (14)</l>
        <l>to that place near Kuḻumūr, in the plain with good cows (5)</l>
        <l>when the capable hillman has joined the falling shade, (4)</l>
        <l>while the elephant bull embraces his dark female adorned with recent birth (9)</l>
        <l>[and] at the same time guards the sleep of [his] calf with swaying gait, (10)</l>
        <l>on the side of the big mountain, where waterfalls roar, (8)</l>
        <l>sounds rising as if from the kitchen of Utiyaṉ (7)</l>
        <l>whose heart does not shy away from what is said [to be] the duty of giving, (6)</l>
        <l>while the strong tiger with sickle[-shaped] stripes [and] fierce eyes,</l>
        <l>when going [out] so that lair that contained [it remains] lonely, roars in stony caverns, (11f.)</l>
        <l>at night when the forest people doze. (13)</l>
      </lg>
        </div>
    </body>
  </text>

